full_description:

Speaker:: Miroslav Šedivý

Track: PyCon: Python Language
Are you done with the migration to Python 3 or did you involuntarily leave some Python 2 relics in your code? Did you leave it as a backdoor so you can easily return to Python 2 if we find out that the whole Python 3 was a dead-end street?


Recorded at the PyConDE & PyData Berlin 2022 conference, April 11-13 2022.
https://2022.pycon.de
More details at the conference page: https://2022.pycon.de/program/NEEA8M
Twitter: https://twitter.com/pydataberlin
Twitter: https://twitter.com/pyconde
